node.text:
While the past few months have been tough for us all, it’s important to remember there’s still good being done in our community. To highlight some of the amazing work being done in Miami, I paid a visit to @joshuasheart on behalf of @jiffylubeintl and Do More to learn all about how Mrs. Mona Lissa Emeran is using her vehicle to give back.
Do More celebrates people who are serving their community through use of their cars — twice a week, Mona Lissa collects fresh bread and pastries from local bakeries to add to Joshua’s Heart meal deliveries, in hopes of giving recipients a wholesome meal and sense of normalcy during these times. On behalf of Jiffy Lube, I was honored to recognize Mona Lissa’s efforts with a year’s worth of free vehicle maintenance services to keep her on the road and helping the community!
Take a look and see why she’s driving to do more, what inspired this amazing selfless act, and the difference it’s making in so many lives. To learn more about Do More or how you can get involved, click the link in my bio or visit JiffyLube.com/DoMore. #Drive2DoMore

node.title: Jiffy Lube International x Do More x Joshua’s Heart Foundation

node.text:
We just wrapped up episode 9 of @searchingformaximumflavor and I am still enamored at the storybook setting of the White Barn Inn Restaurant. This restaurant is a 5-Diamond/5-Star establishment. There aren’t that many that hold those two ratings simultaneously. Find out what deliciousness we enjoyed once the Maine episode is released! 
#searchingformaximumflavor
